      <h1>
       <span style="font-weight: 400">
        <font size="5">
         American Sign Language: "happy"
        </font>
       </span>
       <br/>
      </h1>
      <blockquote>
       <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
       <font face="Arial">
        <p align="left">
         <img align="left" height="178" src="/images/happy.gif" width="256"/>
        </p>
        <p align="left">
         The sign for "happy"
is made by placing one or both of your hands in front of you.
        </p>
        <p align="left">
         Use "flat" hands, palms pointing back.  Circle your 
	hands forward, down, back, up, 
forward, down, back, up.  Both hands move at the same time and
in the same direction. On the upward swing the hands are very close to your 
chest or touch your chest.  On the downward swing your hands are further 
away from your chest.
         <p align="left">
          Note: Some people slightly "slap" the chest - other
people don't even touch.
          <br/>
          <br/>
          Note:  During casual everyday use this sign is 
	sometimes done with just one 
hand.  When used in the song "Happy Birthday to You" it is typically done 
with two hands.
         </p>
        </p>
